\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 16. E. serbicum} Pancic,{\i  Verh. Zool.-Bot. Ges. Wien}{\b  6}: 520 (1856). Perennial; stems 40 75 cm. Basal leaves persistent slightly coriaceous; lamina palmatisect; segments 10-25 × 0·2-4 cm, 5-7, linear, undivided, with soft ascending marginal spines; petiole winged, sometimes broadly sheathing, often with linear, spinescent-dentate to -pinnatisect appendages in upper part. Inflorescence with usually numerous pedunculate, hemispherical capitula 1-1·5 cm. Bracts 1-4 cm, 5-7, linear-acuminate, often expanded at base, with 1-2 pairs of spinescent teeth; bracteoles 3-cuspidate. Sepals 2-3 mm, ovate-lanceolate, shortly aristate. {\i Dry places. • Srbija.} Ju.
\par

