\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 17. E. palmatum} Pancic & Vis.,{\i  Mem. Ist. Veneto }{\b 15}: 20 (1870). Perennial; stems 30-75 cm. Basal leaves persistent, slightly coriaceous; lamina 5-9 × 5-11 cm, reniform-orbicular, palmatisect with 5-7 oblanceolate, mostly 3-fid, serrate lobes; petiole unwinged. Inflorescence strict, green, with up to 10 pedunculate, hemispherical capitula 1-1·5 cm. Bracts 2-4 cm, 5-7, linear-oblanceolate, with 1-5 pairs of spinescent teeth; bracteoles 3-cuspidate. Sepals c. 3 mm, ovate-lanceolate, aristate. Fruit densely scaly. {\i Dry places and woods. • C. part of Balkan peninsula.} Al Bu Gr Ju.
\par

